        "Description": {
            "val": "Global Combat Support System - Marine Corps\/Logistics Chain Management (GCSS-MC\/LCM) Family of Systems (FoS) serves as the primary technology enabler for the Marine Corps Logistics Modernization strategy.  GCSS-MC\/LCM provides the backbone for all logistics information required by Marine Forces and the Supporting Establishment. The core for GCSS-MC\/LCM Increment 1 is a modern, commercial-off-the-shelf enterprise resource planning software (Oracle e-Business Suite).  The  Increment 1 design focused on enabling the warfighter to operate while deployed with reach back to Garrison from the battlefield. Increment 1 replaced 5 legacy supply and maintenance information technology systems and currently supports ~22,000 users world-wide. The focus of future functions will be enhancing capabilities in the areas of warehousing, distribution, logistics planning, decision support, depot maintenance, and integration with emerging technologies to improve asset visibility."
        },
        "Justification": {
            "val": "FY 2020: $4.484M Funding continues to support the ongoing need for technology refresh of hardware and software in support of the sustainment of GCSS-MC\/LCM Increment 1. The funding increase from FY2019 to FY2020 of $4.484M is in support of expanding the fielding of Warehousing Automated Information Technology hardware beyond the major logistics hubs, Supply Management Units (SMU), Repairable Issue Points (RIP), and Initial Issue Points (IIP) to the 140 operating force units' warehouses and storage sites across all three Marine Expeditionary Forces (MEF). This expansion to using units is a significant increase to the quantities in service. It will also support improvements to inventory management and asset visibility for USMC ground forces.  Specifically, efficiency will be realized and come in the form of data accuracy through bar code availability instead of manual data input and in the ability to conduct annual rapid inventory management of install base items throughout the MEFs.\n\nFY2021 Base Appropriation Request: $1.587M Funding will continue to support the ongoing need for technology refresh of hardware and software for the major logistics hubs in support of the sustainment of GCSS-MC\/LCM Increment 1.  Funding decrease from FY2020 to FY2021 of $2.897M is due to the completion of the initial procurement of Warehouse Automated Information Technology Hardware beyond the major logistics hubs."
        },
